
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 06 of Thoracic MRT

When I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Pleural thickening/Mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I know' radio button is enabled
And I select 'Characterization I' tab

Then 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled

And 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Local' radio button is enabled

And 'Size' input field is enabled

And 'Cirumscribed' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-circumscribed' radio button is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Round' radio button is enabled
And 'Lobulated' radio button is enabled
And 'Broad-based' radio button is enabled
And 'Pedunculated' radio button is enabled
And 'Pleural thickening' radio button is enabled

And 'Obtuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Acute' radio button is enabled


When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Histology known' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Histology known' checkbox
Then 'Benign' radio button is enabled
And 'Malignant' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Local' radio button
Then 'Apical' radio button is enabled
And 'Basal' radio button is enabled
And 'Anterior' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lateral' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fissural' checkbox is enabled
And 'Mediastinal' checkbox is enabled

When I enter any value between 1 and 300 in 'Size' input field
Then '2nd plane' input field is enabled

When I enter any value between 1 and 300 in '2nd plane' input field
Then '3rd plane' input field is enabled
